<strong>Distance:</strong> 5.8 km loop &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> ~1 h 55 min &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Elevation Gain:</strong> 236 m
</div>

<p>Follow the classic UNESCO circuit that threads past Shinkyo Bridge before weaving through the cedar-lined approach to Rinnoji Temple, Toshogu Shrine, and Futarasan Shrine. The route combines stone-paved avenues, mossy stairways, and wooded paths, giving you a full sweep of Nikko’s sacred architecture and serene forest scenery.</p>

<p>AllTrails highlights the blend of cultural treasures and gentle inclines that make this walk approachable for most visitors while still offering glimpses of Nikko’s mountainous backdrop. Expect occasional crowds near the shrine precincts, but quieter stretches emerge as you loop through Tamozawa Imperial Villa Park and the residential lanes back toward downtown.</p>

